												<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/alexbollen/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/alex-bollen-photo-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/alex-bollen-photo-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Alex Bollen" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/alexbollen/">Alex Bollen</a></h6>
													Alex Bollen is a the author of <em>Motherdom: Breaking Free from Bad Science and Good Mother Myths</em>researcher with over twenty years of experience, including as a former director of the research agency Ipsos MORI. She is a Postnatal Practitioner with the NCT, the UK’s largest parenting charity, and has been running postnatal groups for new mothers in South West London for over a decade. She is the mother of two children.																									</div>
											</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
										</div>

